# Next.js 15 App Router Patterns

## File Structure & Conventions

-   Use `app/` directory for all pages and components
-   Follow Next.js 15 file-based routing conventions
-   Use `page.tsx` for route pages
-   Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
-   Use `loading.tsx` for loading states
-   Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries

## Page Components

-   Export as default functions
-   Use proper TypeScript types
-   Implement proper metadata when needed
-   Use Next.js Image component for images
-   Implement proper loading and error states

## Layout Structure

-   Use nested layouts for complex page hierarchies
-   Keep layouts focused and reusable
-   Implement proper metadata in root layout
-   Use proper HTML semantic structure

## Data Fetching

-   Use Server Components by default
-   Implement Client Components only when needed
-   Use proper async/await patterns
-   Plan for future Supabase integration

## Routing Patterns

-   Use dynamic routes with `[param]` syntax
-   Implement proper route groups when needed
-   Use parallel routes for complex layouts
-   Implement proper 404 handling

## Performance Optimizations

-   Use Turbopack for development
-   Implement proper image optimization
-   Use Next.js built-in performance features
-   Consider code splitting strategies

## Metadata & SEO

-   Use proper metadata objects
-   Implement Open Graph tags
-   Use semantic HTML elements
-   Ensure proper accessibility attributes
